content:
if 0 == tonumber(settings.get("miner.is_setup",0)) then
    shell.run("miner/sethome.lua")
    
    settings.set("motd.enable",false)
    settings.set("miner.is_exc",0)
    settings.set("miner.lastDepth",0)
    settings.set("miner.exc_rad",20)
    settings.set("miner.sdepth",10)
    settings.set("miner.mdepth",999)
    settings.set("miner.wander",0)
    settings.set("miner.is_setup",1)
    settings.set("miner.autoinc",1)
    settings.set("miner.done",0)
    settings.save(".settings")
end

local function openNet()
    if rednet.isOpen() then
        return true
    else
        local sides = peripheral.getNames()
        for i = 1,#sides do
            if peripheral.getType(sides[i]) == "modem" then
                rednet.open(sides[i])
                if rednet.isOpen() then return true end
            end
        end
    end
    return false
end

local netok = openNet()
if netok then
    local x,y,z = gps.locate()
    if x ~= nil then
        rednet.broadcast({x,y,z},"excgps")
        print("Sent location",x,y,z)
    else
        netok = false
    end
end
if not netok then
    print("ERROR could not broadcast start location")
end

if 0 ~= tonumber(settings.get("miner.done",0)) then
    print("Mining complete! Run 'miner/sethome.lua' or manually edit settings to continue mining.")
    return
end

print("Entering infinite mining mode...")

local auto = 0 ~= tonumber(settings.get("miner.autoinc",1))

while shell.run("miner/excgps.lua") and auto do
    sleep(1)
end

  n, k = map(int, f.readline().strip().split())
  arr = list(map(int, f.readline().strip().split()))
k += 1
# print(arr)
setArr = set(arr[0:k - 1])
# print(setArr)
for i in range(len(arr) - k + 1):
  setArr.add(arr[i+k - 1])
  # print(setArr, arr[i:i+k])
  if len(setArr) != k:
    print('YES')
    n = 0
    break
  setArr.remove(arr[i])
  
if n != 0:
  print('NO')

title: Use ChatGPT API On Linux To Ask Question Using Command
content:
Use ChatGPT API On Linux To Ask Question Using Command

>>>

Since OpenAI released ChatGPT, users have casually experimented with the tool. This powerful AI tool benefits content creators, influencers, and programmers. etc. For cyber security researchers and ethical hackers, it can be more helpful in different ways for different objectives like bug hunting, security questions, etc., and research on particular vulnerabilities without wasting time on googling things and visiting multiple websites.

In this article, we guide you on how to install ChatGPT on your Linux so you can easily ask your queries to AI using your command-line interface (Terminal).

Follow these simple steps:
1. First you have to generate and copy your API key by signing up on OpenAI official website.
2. Type the following commands on your Linux terminal.

• sudo pip3 install openai
• git clone https://github.com/mglantz/chatgpt
• cd chatgpt && sudo cp gpt.py /usr/bin
• export OPENAI_API_KEY=<paste your api key here>
• gpt.py "What is ChatGPT?"

Now you can see the output of ChatGPT on your terminal and this can be very useful, especially for bug hunters in their penetration testing.

I hope this information is helpful for you and make sure to connect with us on social handles to never miss new updates.

title: estruc logicas
content:
#!/usr/bin/env python
# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
"""
Script que pide un nombre y una edad y lo saluda en broma
EJ:
>> Ingrese su nombre: Juan
>> Ingrese su edad: 23
>> Hola Juan, usted tiene 23 años pero parece de 46

nombre = input("Ingrese su nombre: ")
edad = int(input("Ingrese su edad: "))

print("Hola",nombre + ", usted tiene",edad,"años pero parece de",edad*2)

print(f"Hola {nombre}, usted tiene {edad} años pero parece de {edad*2:.4f}")


# 1 condicional (if), 1 bucle indefinido (while), 1 bucle definido (for)
# Script que pide una edad y responde si es mayor

edad = int(input("Ingrese su edad: "))

if edad >= 18:
    print("Eres mayor")
    print("Jaja")

else:
    print("Eres menor")
    print("Jaja")

print("Chau")


# Script que pide un nro de mes y devuelve el trimestre al cual pertenece
mes = int(input("Ingrese un nro de mes: "))

if  1 <= mes <= 3:
    print("Primer trimestre")

elif 4 <= mes <= 6:
    print("Segundo trimestre")
    
elif 7 <= mes <= 9:
    print("Tercer trimestre")
    
elif 10 <= mes <= 12:
    print("Cuarto trimestre")

else:
    print("Error en el nro de mes")

"""
# Script que imprime una lista
lista = [1,2,3,4,5,6]

i = 0
while i < len(lista):
    print(lista[i])
    i += 1

for numero in lista:
    print(numero)
    
for numero in range(6,-1,-1):
    print(numero)

title: How To Make A Main Menu In Roblox Studio
content:
local CurrentCamera = workspace.CurrentCamera

local CameraPartName = "CameraPart"
local TransitionTime = 1


local CameraPart = script.Parent:FindFirstChild(CameraPartName)

repeat wait()
	CurrentCamera.CameraType = Enum.CameraType.Scriptable
until CurrentCamera.CameraType == Enum.CameraType.Scriptable
CurrentCamera.CFrame = CameraPart.CFrame

script.Parent.MouseButton1Click:Connect(function()

	local SlidingEffectFrame = Instance.new("Frame")
	SlidingEffectFrame.BorderSizePixel = 0
	SlidingEffectFrame.Size = UDim2.new(1,0,1,0)
	SlidingEffectFrame.Position = UDim2.new(1,0,0,0)
	SlidingEffectFrame.Parent = script:FindFirstAncestorWhichIsA("ScreenGui")
	SlidingEffectFrame:TweenPosition(UDim2.new(0,0,0,0), Enum.EasingDirection.InOut, Enum.EasingStyle.Sine, TransitionTime/2, false)
	wait(TransitionTime/2)
	repeat wait()
		CurrentCamera.CameraType = Enum.CameraType.Custom
	until CurrentCamera.CameraType == Enum.CameraType.Custom
	for _, instance in pairs(script:FindFirstAncestorWhichIsA("ScreenGui"):GetChildren()) do
		if instance ~= SlidingEffectFrame then
			instance.Visible = false
		end
	end

	SlidingEffectFrame:TweenPosition(UDim2.new(-1,0,0,0), Enum.EasingDirection.InOut, Enum.EasingStyle.Sine, TransitionTime/2, false)

end)

title: icue removal
content:
The guide to uninstall iCUE are as follows.  It does involve removing registry files.

Open your computer's Control Panel.
Open the Programs and Features options.
Select Corsair Utility Engine in the list, and then select Uninstall.
Press Window Key + R to open the Run command.
Type %appdata% and press Enter.
Delete any Corsair folders in the window that pops up.
Return to the Run window and type %localappdata%.
Delete any Corsair folders in the window that pops up.
Open File Explorer and navigate to C:\Program Files (x86)\ for iCUE 3, or C:\Program Files\ for iCUE 4.
Delete any Corsair folders in that folder.
Type Regedit in the Run window and then click OK.
Go to HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\ and delete the Corsair folder.
Go to HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\ and delete the Corsair folder.
Restart your computer.
Download a new installer file for iCUE from Corsair.com and reinstall.
The way the fans work in the Corsair One is that they're connected to the main CPU PUMP which connects to the USB 2.0 header on your motherboard.  This is how the fan interacts with iCUE.  When iCUE isn't running, the fans will default to a pre-programmed hardware curve that's built into the CPU PUMP.  It essentially acts as the main controller for the fan.

title: Untitled
TurbineControl.lua
content:
b = peripheral.wrap("powah:energy_cell_1")
r = peripheral.wrap("BigReactors-Reactor_3")
t = peripheral.wrap("BigReactors-Turbine_2")
m = peripheral.wrap("monitor_2")
while true do
    bCap = b.getEnergyCapacity()
    bCur = b.getEnergy()
    bP = bCur/bCap*100
    rstate = r.getActive()
    tProd = math.floor(t.getEnergyProducedLastTick())
    tSpeed = t.getRotorSpeed()
    tCoilState = t.getInductorEngaged()
    if (bP >=99 and rstate)
    then
        r.setActive(false)
    end
    
    if (bP <=15 and not rstate)
    then
        r.setActive(true)
        t.setInductorEngaged(false)
    end
    
    if (rstate and not tCoilState and tSpeed >=1795)
    then
        t.setInductorEngaged(true)
    end    

    if tCoilState
    then
        tOn = "on."
    else
        tOn = "off."
    end
    
    print("Battery Percent: " .. bP .. " Reactor State " .. tostring(rstate))
    m.clear()
    m.setCursorPos(1,1)
    m.write("Battery Percent: " .. math.floor(bP))
    m.setCursorPos(1,2)
    m.write("Turbine is " .. tOn)
    m.setCursorPos(1,3)
    m.write("Turbine is producing " .. tProd .. "FE/t")
    sleep(2)

end

Bem-vindo à Arcane! Criado em novembro de 2021, nosso rpg é baseado no universo mitológico e de Percy Jackson, incluindo não somente os panteões gregos e romanos, mas também aqueles que sua imaginação desejar. Possuímos um sistema completo garantindo uma experiência imersiva e empolgante, perfeita para desenvolver suas histórias. Aqui, você é livre para criar e desenvolver a história de seu personagem!
